Per the [[2010 US Census]], Chestnut had 246 people. Among non-Hispanics this includes 233 [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1 [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]], 3 [[Asian American|Asian]], 2 of two or more races, and 7 [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]].

The population was spread out, with 72.0% over the age of 18 and 15.4% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 37.5 years. The gender ratio was 47.6% male and 52.4% female. Among 99 occupied households, 88 were owner-occupied and 11 were renter-occupied.<ref>[https://archive.today/20190521214830/https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_DP_DPDP1&prodType=table Factfinder, Census.gov]</ref>

